SUMMARY:Benefit show 15$ for comunities of Masafer Yatta\, Palestine
LOCATION:1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-18 19:30:00\n\n1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797\n\nALL EYES ON MASAFER YATTA\nMa
 safer Yatta is a collection of 19 villages in the South Hebron Hills of th
 e West Bank\, Palestine. This rural region is considered "Area C"\, which 
 are territories of the West Bank that are under complete control of the Is
 raeli government and it's occupation force and make up more than 60% of th
 e West Bank. While Palestinians in these areas are subjected to millitary 
 checkpoints which they cant cross without special permits\, the Israeli ap
 artheid law allows Israeli citizens to have complete freedom of movement t
 hrough these areas\, areas that are used as a large and important part in 
 the zionist settler project of greater Israel. The zionist regime tactical
 ly places violent settlers on hills over the Palestinian villages. Protect
 ed by the law\, the army and the police\, the settlers use physical and ps
 ychological terror on the Palestinians with the goal of running them out o
 f their villages and taking over. This system of violence and intimidation
  backed up by the law creates a living environment of constant danger and 
 fear\, and we see the situation escalating day by day - communites attacke
 d\, villages burnt and destroyed and Palestinians having everything taken 
 away from them while the settlers are getting more and more power. Masafer
  Yatta is an area which is extremely prone to attacks\, where not a day go
 es by peacefully. Any attempt by the Palestinians to resist their living b
 eing taken away from them can result in arrests\, violence or worse - loss
  of lives.\nOn April 11th\, people in many different cities across differe
 nt continents are standing up\, raising their voices and organizing\, both
  to collect money for those communites so they can hopefully recover and r
 ebuild what is taken from them by the israeli occupation\, as well as to s
 how solidarity with the Palestinians living under the occupation of the vi
 olent zionist regime - and to state we will keep fighting until its fall.\
 nThe Montreal show is gonna happen on April 18th as there is already a ben
 efit gig for Noise Not Borders on April 11th\, but we will have a donation
  stand at that gig as well so come see us!\nDoors : 7:30 pm\nShow : 8:30 p
 m\nSynaptic Isolation Syndrome - Fast Crust\, Montreal\nVarices - Grindcor
 e\, Sherbrooke\nMigración Animal - Crust Punk\, Montreal\nAt B7 (1900 rue
  Le Ber)\n15$ at the door\nAll ages\nKeep resisting\nKeep fighting\nLong l
 ive Palestine\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-33
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260411T035051
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T120000
