SUMMARY:D.I.Y. Skill Sharing Day
LOCATION:1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-19 13:00:00\n\n1900 Le Ber (métro Charlevoix)\n\nhttp
 s://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797\n\nTDN - Technological Disobedie
 nce Network\nBatiment 7\n1900 Rue Le Ber\, Montreal\nApril 19th\, 1pm-7pm\
 nWe collectively - punks\, fuckups\, queers\, anarchists - have all the sk
 ills we need to reject techno-fascism.\nWe want people to come share their
  D.I.Y. practices to strengthen the mutual aid networks in place\, and hop
 efully build new ones.\nWe're putting on a D.I.Y. skill sharing day\, with
  stations and workshops. We'll cover subjects like bike and auto mechanics
 \, DIY air purifiers\, FOSS software\, plants grafting\, vermicompost and 
 more. Schedule available at the door.\nWe'll have a space to share thought
 s on what self-sufficiency actually means to us\, and what we can do right
  now towards it.\nThe event is PWYC\, no one will be turned away for lack 
 of funds. Masks and hand sanitizer will be provided at the door. The venue
  is wheelchair accessible.\nBRING THINGS TO FIX!\nElectronics\, bikes\, cl
 othes (to fix and/or donate)\, or anything else you want to bring
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/6074430797
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-35
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260411T035051
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T170000
SUMMARY:Violet Hour Book Club: "Starry Night"
LOCATION:6450 avenue Christophe-Colomb
DESCRIPTION:2026-04-19 15:00:00\n\n6450 avenue Christophe-Colomb\n\nhttps:
 //www.openstreetmap.org/way/1080082859\n\nJoin us for the next meeting of 
 the Violet Hour Book Club\, a reading group devoted to classic and contemp
 orary works of LGBTQ literature. The book we will be discussing is Starry 
 Starry Night (2025) by Shani Mootoo.\nToustes sont invités·es au Violet 
 Hour Book Club\, et chacun.e est bienvenu.e à partager ses pensées sur l
 e livre en anglais ou en français.\nWe will be meeting at Espace des Poss
 ibles Petite-Patrie (1052 Beaubien Street East\, Beaubien Metro). L’Espa
 ce des Possibles a comme mission d’offrir un lieu d’entraide\, d’app
 rentissages et d’implication dédié à la transition sociale et écolog
 ique (la transition socio-écologique).\nThe space is given to us for free
 \, but VHBC participants are welcome to make voluntary contributions to he
 lp support our mandate to create LGBTQ literary events for Montrealers.\nA
  reminder: All VHBC titles are available at Librairie Paragraphe Bookstore
  (2220\, McGill College Ave) at 15% off and at Librairie Pulp Books &amp\;
  Cafe (3952 Wellington St.) at 10% off.\nABOUT THE BOOK ///\nIn Starry Sta
 rry Night\, Mootoo gives us the singular voice of Anju Ghoshal\, a young g
 irl living in 1960s Trinidad. Through Anju’s innocent and clear-eyed obs
 ervations\, the reader becomes both a witness to and a participant in her 
 negotiations of an unexpectedly new and complex life\, spanning from the a
 ges of four to twelve.\nSet against the backdrop of a politically exciting
  time in Trinidad’s history\, just before and after it gained independen
 ce\, we meet Anju’s beloved Ma and Pa and her socially advancing family.
  While preoccupied with their own dramas\, the adults around her often fai
 l to recognize the needs of the children who depend on them.\nBeautifully 
 crafted and rich with sumptuous detail\, this unique narrative coalesces i
 nto a portrait of a child who\, despite her privileged appearance\, must u
 ltimately fend for herself because her safety depends on it.\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/1080082859
END:VEVENT
